Claude (via MCP)Cursor IDE <p>Add to your Claude configuration:</p> <pre><code>{
  "mcpServers": {
    "rapidtriage": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["@/-mcp"],
      "env": {
        "BROWSER_TOOLS_PORT": "1421"
      }
    }
  }
}
</code></pre> <p>Add to <code>.cursor/mcp_settings.json</code>:</p> <pre><code>{
  "mcpServers": {
    "rapidtriage": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["/path/to/rapidtriage-mcp/dist/mcp-server.js"],
      "env": {
        "BROWSER_TOOLS_PORT": "1421"
      }
    }
  }
}
</code></pre>

Kill existing processUse different portCheck system permissions <pre><code># Kill the process using port 1421
kill -9 12345

# Or kill all Node.js processes
pkill -f node

# Then restart
npx @/-server
</code></pre> <pre><code># Set custom port
export RAPIDTRIAGE_PORT=3030
npx @/-server

# Update MCP configuration
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "rapidtriage": {
      "env": {
        "BROWSER_TOOLS_PORT": "3030"
      }
    }
  }
}
</code></pre> <pre><code># On macOS/Linux, check if port requires sudo
# Ports &lt; 1024 require root privileges

# Use unprivileged port instead
export RAPIDTRIAGE_PORT=8080
npx @/-server
</code></pre>

Fix IDE ConfigurationCheck Node.js PathInstall Global Package <pre><code>// Cursor: ~/.cursor/mcp_settings.json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "rapidtriage": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["@/-mcp"],
      "env": {
        "BROWSER_TOOLS_PORT": "1421",
        "BROWSER_TOOLS_HOST": "localhost"
      }
    }
  }
}
</code></pre> <pre><code># Find Node.js installation
which node
which npx

# Use absolute paths if needed
{
  "command": "/usr/local/bin/npx",
  "args": ["@/-mcp"]
}
</code></pre> <pre><code># Install globally first
npm install -g @/-mcp

# Then use direct command
{
  "command": "rapidtriage-mcp",
  "args": []
}
</code></pre>

Adjust Cache SettingsMonitor Memory Usage <pre><code>// rapidtriage.config.json
{
  "features": {
    "networking": {
      "maxLogEntries": 500,
      "maxNetworkEntries": 250
    }
  },
  "server": {
    "cleanupInterval": 60000
  }
}
</code></pre> <pre><code># Monitor server memory
ps aux | grep rapidtriage

# Check Chrome memory usage
# Open chrome://memory-internals/
</code></pre>

Optimize Screenshot SettingsCheck Page Complexity <pre><code>{
  "options": {
    "fullPage": false,
    "quality": 60,
    "format": "jpeg",
    "optimizeForSpeed": true
  }
}
</code></pre> <pre><code>// Check DOM size in browser console
console.log('DOM elements:', document.querySelectorAll('*').length);
console.log('Images:', document.querySelectorAll('img').length);
console.log('Scripts:', document.querySelectorAll('script').length);
</code></pre>
